Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:2352):
`jobIdOrCorrelationFilter` is used both to client-filter `filteredJobs` and as a server query param in `buildJobsParams()`, but the input doesn’t trigger `loadJobs()` / reset pagination when it changes. This can leave `jobsNextCursor` from an unfiltered query in place while subsequent “Load More” / auto-refresh requests send a different `jobIdOrCorrelation` value, which can produce inconsistent results or an invalid cursor on the backend. Consider either (a) making this field purely client-side (remove it from `buildJobsParams()`), or (b) treating it as a server-side search by debouncing an `@input`/`@change` handler that calls `loadJobs()` with no cursor (clearing `jobs`/`jobsNextCursor` for the new query).

Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, treat jobIdOrCorrelationFilter as a server-backed deliveries search because buildJobsParams() already sends it as jobIdOrCorrelation. Add a small debounced input handler for the deliveries search input that reloads from the first page: define a module-scope timeout handle (for example let jobsSearchDebounce: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null), add a function such as queueJobSearchReload() that clears any existing timeout and after about 300ms calls loadJobs() with no cursor. Wire the input at the Job or correlation field (currently v-model="jobIdOrCorrelationFilter") with @input="queueJobSearchReload". Do not call loadJobs(jobsNextCursor) from this handler; the reload must clear jobsNextCursor via the existing !cursor path in loadJobs(). Keep filteredJobs computed in place as a client-side refinement of the loaded server results, and keep linkToDeliveries() calling loadJobs() immediately when deliveries have already loaded.
